From 4368bd19243a447b7b959962973bf26d15d00832 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PreCareBot Dev <dev@example.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 22:36:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PR27: rounding-summary / escalation-breakdown analytics +
 Grafana dashboards

- backend/db/repositories.py: list_all_rounding_sessions(),
  list_all_patient_interactions() -- same 'unfiltered, for analytics'
  role as PR10's list_all_care_requests() etc.
- backend/services/analytics_service.py: rounding_summary() and
  escalation_breakdown(). patients_detected / interactions_started are
  derived from each session's *current* status (safe here since reaching
  either milestone is a strict prerequisite no matter which branch a
  session eventually takes); escalations_created / urgent_escalations are
  counted directly from nurse_escalations rows instead, since an
  escalated session and a plain INFORMATION_ONLY session can share the
  same final COMPLETED status -- status alone can't tell them apart.
  escalation_breakdown()'s by_detected_need groups by each escalation's
  parent rounding_sessions.detected_need (always set before an escalation
  can be raised), not escalations.reason (caller-supplied, optional).
- backend/api/routes_analytics.py: GET /analytics/rounding-summary, GET
  /analytics/escalation-breakdown.
- grafana/provisioning/dashboards/rounding-overview.json (new): session
  count, patients detected, needs classified, escalations created,
  urgent count, average ack time (stat panels) + daily session count
  (timeseries).
- grafana/provisioning/dashboards/escalation-queue.json (new): pending
  count, average ack time (stat panels), priority/need breakdown
  (piecharts), status breakdown (table).
- tests/test_analytics_service.py: 14 new tests, including one proving
  patients_detected/interactions_started/needs_classified are NOT
  overcounted for a session that stalls partway through.
- tests/test_api_analytics_rounding.py (new): 3 API-level tests -- no
  API-level analytics tests existed before this PR (only service-layer),
  so this covers just the two new endpoints, matching this PR's scope.
- tests/test_grafana_config.py: regression guard that rounding_sessions/
  patient_interactions/nurse_escalations are actually queried by some
  dashboard, plus the file-count check bumped to >=5.

Verified: 233 non-pybullet tests pass (221 previous + 12 more here);
ruff clean; mypy clean against full backend/perception/vision scope;
both new dashboard JSON files parse and pass the existing generic
grafana config checks (datasource reference, valid JSON, etc.).
